WEBVTT

00:02.403 --> 00:02.870
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:29.097 --> 00:32.633
[ Snoring ]

00:32.666 --> 00:33.834
Who? What?

00:33.867 --> 00:36.370
[ Dramatic music plays ]

00:45.179 --> 00:47.381
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:47.415 --> 00:48.782
♪♪

00:48.816 --> 00:51.785
Aaaaaaaah!

00:57.991 --> 01:00.661
Yeah,
it's a secret, apparently.

01:00.694 --> 01:02.463
[ Rumbling ]
Hmm?

01:02.496 --> 01:04.064
Arghhhh!

01:04.098 --> 01:06.234
What did you
just say?!
[ Screams ]

01:06.267 --> 01:09.470
Aah!
[ Screams ]

01:09.503 --> 01:11.939
Son, what did you
just say?!

01:11.972 --> 01:13.707
I said...
[ Screams ]

01:13.741 --> 01:15.543
Before that!
There's an urban legend

01:15.576 --> 01:19.380
about a secret menu
at Joyful Burger!

01:20.181 --> 01:21.615
You have
my attention.

01:21.649 --> 01:24.385
The most secret item on it
is a burger.

01:24.418 --> 01:27.321
It is said that the burger
does not exist

01:27.355 --> 01:29.257
until someone speaks its name.

01:29.290 --> 01:32.126
It must be summoned
from the other side.

01:32.160 --> 01:34.828
Wait, isn't that
how you order food anyway?

01:34.862 --> 01:36.197
You don't get it, dude.

01:36.230 --> 01:37.765
Apparently,
this burger is so hard core,

01:37.798 --> 01:40.934
it qualifies as breakfast,
lunch, and dinner

01:40.968 --> 01:43.137
for seven people
for seven years.

01:43.171 --> 01:47.375
And they say that if you eat it
in 15 minutes, they'll pay.

01:47.408 --> 01:49.477
Pay for the burger?
No,
your hospital fees.

01:49.510 --> 01:50.711
[ Gasps ]

01:50.744 --> 01:53.281
This is the burger
that I've been searching for

01:53.314 --> 01:54.482
all my life.

01:54.515 --> 01:56.950
My Atlantis,
my Montezuma's gold,

01:56.984 --> 01:59.520
my Moby Dick...

01:59.553 --> 02:02.223
Except not literally,
as I already ate a white whale.

02:02.256 --> 02:03.824
There's only
one problem, Dad.

02:03.857 --> 02:06.227
You can't order it
without knowing its name.

02:06.260 --> 02:08.095
[ Brakes squeal ]

02:08.128 --> 02:10.964
Man: Welcome to Joyful Burger!
Can I take your order?

02:10.998 --> 02:12.032
[ Chuckles ]

02:12.065 --> 02:13.301
Yes, I'd like

02:13.334 --> 02:14.868
a secret [imitates static]
burger, please.

02:14.902 --> 02:17.104
Uh, could you
repeat your order, sir?

02:17.137 --> 02:18.606
[ Groans ]
Yes, I would like

02:18.639 --> 02:21.074
the secret [Imitates static]
burger, please.

02:21.108 --> 02:22.776
Uh, excuse me?
Listen, little man!

02:22.810 --> 02:24.545
I'm the [Imitates static]
customer here,

02:24.578 --> 02:26.514
and I [Imitates static] don't
want to have to repeat my order!

02:26.547 --> 02:28.616
[ Imitates static ] One secret
[Imitates static] burger to go,

02:28.649 --> 02:30.218
you little
[Imitates static]!

02:30.251 --> 02:31.585
I'm sorry, sir,
but that's not an intercom.

02:31.619 --> 02:34.021
Can I take
your order please?

02:34.054 --> 02:36.324
One [Imitates static]
Burger!

02:36.357 --> 02:37.825
Uh, for real?

02:37.858 --> 02:39.393
Was I not
clear enough?

02:39.427 --> 02:41.762
Uh, have it
your way, sir.

02:41.795 --> 02:42.863
[ Laughs ]

02:42.896 --> 02:45.065
[ Snorts, spits ]

02:45.098 --> 02:46.667
[ Groans ]

02:46.700 --> 02:48.502
Mm.

02:48.536 --> 02:51.104
He meant
the secret burger!

02:51.138 --> 02:52.306
I see.

02:52.340 --> 02:53.541
And what is the name

02:53.574 --> 02:54.942
of the aforementioned
secret burger?

02:54.975 --> 02:56.477
Ah, I got it.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.145
It's called the Vein Thickener!
The Deep Fried Thrombosis!

02:58.178 --> 02:59.480
The Meat Your Maker?
The Heart-Breaker!

02:59.513 --> 03:00.948
The Bun-dertaker!
The Commander In Beef!

03:00.981 --> 03:02.149
The Bowel-Buster!

03:02.182 --> 03:03.717
No?
More mysterious maybe...

03:03.751 --> 03:05.986
The Illumi-patty!
The Area Beefty-One?

03:06.019 --> 03:07.655
The Bilderburger!
Come on, man!

03:07.688 --> 03:09.257
You know
what we're talking about!

03:09.290 --> 03:10.458
Maybe.

03:10.491 --> 03:11.659
But I can't
serve you something

03:11.692 --> 03:13.227
you don't even
know the name of.

03:13.261 --> 03:14.762
There's only
so many names it could be.

03:14.795 --> 03:16.397
We just need to figure out
which one.

03:16.430 --> 03:18.366
You mean
figure out sand-which one.

03:18.399 --> 03:19.767
Dude,
stop with the puns.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.869
I can't!
I've fallen down the pun hole!

03:21.902 --> 03:23.437
I've gone so deep,
I'm punderground!

03:23.471 --> 03:24.838
What a pun-fortunate
turn of events.

03:24.872 --> 03:26.474
I've pundermined
any respect you had for me.

03:26.507 --> 03:27.708
I don't punderstand
why I --

03:27.741 --> 03:29.343
Ow! Dude,
I know it was annoying,

03:29.377 --> 03:30.911
but it didn't warrant
a punch.

03:30.944 --> 03:32.513
Ow!

03:32.546 --> 03:34.815
That's wasn't even a pun,
that's just what that word is!

03:34.848 --> 03:36.183
So the plan is --

03:36.216 --> 03:38.118
you guys get hired
at Joyful Burger.

03:38.151 --> 03:39.387
Why don't you
get hired?

03:39.420 --> 03:40.654
I can't.
Why?

03:40.688 --> 03:43.056
Uh...because of my
medical condition?

03:43.090 --> 03:44.425
Really?

03:44.458 --> 03:46.427
Well, I get this
allergic reaction to effort.

03:46.460 --> 03:49.597
The symptoms are dangling arms,
constant eye rolls,

03:49.630 --> 03:52.266
and a breathing problem
that makes me sigh a lot.

03:52.300 --> 03:54.302
[ Inhales deeply,
sighs loudly ]

03:54.335 --> 03:56.437
Being lazy
is not a disease, Dad.

03:56.470 --> 03:57.838
No, it's true!
I really have a --

03:57.871 --> 03:59.873
Oh, I can't be bothered
to finish that sentence.

03:59.907 --> 04:01.542
I'll give you 20 bucks
if you do it.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.677
Wow, you've reached
a whole new level of laziness.

04:03.711 --> 04:05.245
You've invented
the reverse job.

04:05.279 --> 04:06.714
But okay. So, what?
We get hired,

04:06.747 --> 04:09.116
and then we look for the name
of the secret burger?

04:09.149 --> 04:10.484
They won't
just tell anyone.

04:10.518 --> 04:11.919
They'll need to trust you,

04:11.952 --> 04:14.121
so, first, you have to be
the best employees ever.

04:14.154 --> 04:18.459
♪♪

04:19.860 --> 04:21.895
[ Gasps ]

04:21.929 --> 04:25.499
♪♪

04:26.534 --> 04:28.902
Huh?

04:30.170 --> 04:33.040
Oh? [ Chuckles ]

04:33.073 --> 04:34.942
♪♪

04:35.776 --> 04:37.945
I don't know
what that secret ingredient is,

04:37.978 --> 04:40.247
but the customers
just love your burgers!

04:40.280 --> 04:42.750
The secret ingredient
is love.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.585
Mm...mm.

04:44.618 --> 04:46.554
[ Cheers and applause ]
Man: Great job.

04:46.587 --> 04:48.522
The board wants you two
as managers.
Ah!

04:48.556 --> 04:49.790
There's only
one problem --

04:49.823 --> 04:51.625
you need to halve
our labor costs.

04:51.659 --> 04:52.826
Both: Ah!

04:52.860 --> 04:55.929
♪♪

05:00.501 --> 05:02.002
[ Applause ]
Great job.

05:02.035 --> 05:03.837
The board wants you
as senior members.

05:03.871 --> 05:06.139
There's only one problem --
you need to double production.

05:06.173 --> 05:07.608
Both: Ah!

05:08.409 --> 05:10.778
[ Cow moos ]

05:11.745 --> 05:14.748
[ Mooing ]

05:14.782 --> 05:16.016
Both: Ah!

05:16.049 --> 05:17.518
[ Groans ]
Great job.

05:17.551 --> 05:19.820
The board wants you
as our new CEOs.

05:19.853 --> 05:22.423
There's only one problem --
you still have hearts.

05:22.456 --> 05:24.157
♪♪

05:24.191 --> 05:26.527
Both: Ah!
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

05:26.560 --> 05:28.261
And in other news,
business moguls

05:28.295 --> 05:29.997
Gumball and Darwin Watterson
have sold

05:30.030 --> 05:32.833
their Joyful Burger shares
for a whopping $4.6 billion.

05:32.866 --> 05:34.868
Our reporter
has an exclusive interview

05:34.902 --> 05:36.637
from their lavish
new mansion.

05:36.670 --> 05:38.338
So how do you feel
about your success?

05:38.372 --> 05:39.540
It's cool.

05:39.573 --> 05:41.108
I mean,
I like the big house,

05:41.141 --> 05:43.143
but it's kind of hard
to communicate with each other.

05:43.176 --> 05:46.113
[ Echoing ] Gumball, can you
pass me the salt, please?

05:47.214 --> 05:49.383
See, I asked him
that last week.

05:49.417 --> 05:51.919
Oh, one moment.

05:51.952 --> 05:55.423
♪♪

06:04.231 --> 06:05.399
[ Door closes ]

06:05.433 --> 06:06.634
Sorry.
You were saying?

06:06.667 --> 06:08.035
What gave you the idea
of getting into

06:08.068 --> 06:10.237
the fast-food industry
in the first place?

06:10.270 --> 06:11.872
Well, it all started
when my father

06:11.905 --> 06:14.708
wanted to try
a secret burger and...

06:14.742 --> 06:16.977
we got
completely sidetracked.

06:22.416 --> 06:25.953
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

06:28.989 --> 06:30.958
Ah? Huh?

06:30.991 --> 06:33.160
Huh? Wha?

06:35.262 --> 06:38.466
Oof!

06:39.299 --> 06:40.901
[ Electricity buzzing ]

06:40.934 --> 06:42.603
Gumball: [ Gruffly ]
Tell us the name

06:42.636 --> 06:43.837
of the secret burger.

06:43.871 --> 06:45.906
Uh...I don't mean
to be disrespectful,

06:45.939 --> 06:47.741
but there's no point
disguising your voice

06:47.775 --> 06:49.477
if you're not wearing any masks.

06:49.510 --> 06:51.912
Dad,
is the deep fryer on?

06:51.945 --> 06:54.915
You can do whatever you like,
but I'll never talk!

06:54.948 --> 06:57.417
Oh, we know there's nothing
we can do to you

06:57.451 --> 06:58.786
to make you talk.

06:58.819 --> 07:01.188
That's why we brought him.

07:01.221 --> 07:03.591
[ Gasps ]
No! Not Burgie!

07:03.624 --> 07:05.559
[ Grunting ]
What are you doing?!

07:05.593 --> 07:07.027
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

07:07.060 --> 07:08.361
No!

07:08.395 --> 07:10.430
Burgie can't be seen
eating our competitor's food!

07:10.464 --> 07:13.033
Please stop!
I can't lose this job!

07:13.066 --> 07:14.468
I only have 37 others!

07:14.502 --> 07:15.903
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

07:15.936 --> 07:16.904
Ah. Please!

07:16.937 --> 07:19.439
Burgie would never
betray the brand!

07:19.473 --> 07:21.709
[ Screams ]
No!

07:21.742 --> 07:25.546
[ Camera shutter clicks ]
Burgie is a friend
to all the children!

07:25.579 --> 07:28.081
♪♪

07:28.115 --> 07:31.418
Hmm?
What?

07:31.451 --> 07:32.720
That's just
how nuggets are made.

07:32.753 --> 07:34.622
Everyone knows that.
[ Groans ]

07:34.655 --> 07:36.890
All right.
You asked for it.

07:37.658 --> 07:39.359
[ Screaming ]

07:39.392 --> 07:41.094
[ Sobbing ]

07:41.128 --> 07:42.496
No! No!

07:42.530 --> 07:44.798
You can't eat Burgie's fingers!

07:44.832 --> 07:48.736
Anything is edible
if you deep-fry it long enough.

07:51.539 --> 07:53.106
[ Muffled ]
I was wrong.

07:53.140 --> 07:55.509
Okay, okay, stop!
I'll tell you!

07:55.543 --> 07:56.710
[ Inhales deeply ]

07:56.744 --> 07:58.111
There is
a secret burger,

07:58.145 --> 07:59.780
but to be deemed worthy enough
to know its name,

07:59.813 --> 08:01.114
first,
you have to eat a burger

08:01.148 --> 08:03.350
from every Joyful Burger
in Elmore.

08:03.383 --> 08:04.585
Pbht! Done!

08:04.618 --> 08:07.320
In one hour.

08:07.354 --> 08:08.989
♪♪

08:09.022 --> 08:10.791
[ Tires screech ]

08:12.392 --> 08:14.562
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]

08:14.595 --> 08:16.897
[ Tires screech ]

08:17.698 --> 08:19.066
[ Tires screech ]

08:19.099 --> 08:20.300
[ Clock ticking ]

08:20.333 --> 08:22.770
[ Tires screech ]
Ah!

08:23.370 --> 08:24.638
[ Tires screech ]

08:24.672 --> 08:26.506
♪♪

08:26.540 --> 08:29.242
[ Tires screech ]

08:29.276 --> 08:30.544
[ Panting ]

08:30.578 --> 08:31.745
Dad!

08:31.779 --> 08:33.581
What's going on
with your face?

08:34.447 --> 08:36.183
I think it's sward!
What's that?

08:36.216 --> 08:38.686
Sweat made out of lard.
[ Both retching ]

08:38.719 --> 08:40.120
[ Clock ticking ]

08:40.153 --> 08:42.222
[ Tires screech ]

08:43.056 --> 08:46.059
[ Panting, groaning ]
Ah!

08:46.093 --> 08:49.362
[ Whistling,
electricity crackles ]

08:49.396 --> 08:50.664
♪♪

08:50.698 --> 08:52.299
[ Engine revs, tires screech ]

08:56.136 --> 08:57.404
[ Grunts ]

08:57.437 --> 08:59.206
You won't fit!

08:59.239 --> 09:00.974
I've got this.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.375
[ Groans ]

09:02.409 --> 09:03.977
Oh, what is that now?!

09:04.011 --> 09:05.879
Sweeze!
Okay, but please
don't tell us what that --

09:05.913 --> 09:07.547
It's sward
made out of cheese!
[ Retching ]

09:07.581 --> 09:09.382
It will lubricate my body,
now push!

09:09.416 --> 09:10.784
[ Both grunting ]

09:10.818 --> 09:13.153
Did you really have to
supersize that last meal?

09:13.186 --> 09:15.756
I'm sorry!
It was just really good value!

09:15.789 --> 09:16.957
[ Tires popping ]

09:16.990 --> 09:18.759
[ Air hisses ]
Darn it.

09:18.792 --> 09:20.193
We're gonna
have to run.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.762
No!!

09:21.795 --> 09:22.996
It's okay,
Mr. Dad.

09:23.030 --> 09:24.865
That's the beauty
of corporate mega-chains

09:24.898 --> 09:26.266
destroying
our neighborhoods.

09:26.299 --> 09:28.736
There's always another one
right across the street.

09:28.769 --> 09:30.704
Like I said...no!

09:30.738 --> 09:33.306
[ Clock ticking ]

09:33.340 --> 09:34.742
[ Both grunting ]

09:34.775 --> 09:36.509
I think
I smell burning.

09:36.543 --> 09:38.679
That's good.
He's burning calories!

09:38.712 --> 09:41.348
No, it's just my thighs
rubbing together.

09:42.349 --> 09:44.017
[ Clock ticking ]

09:45.753 --> 09:47.621
Wa-wa-wait --
You can't eat that!

09:47.655 --> 09:49.322
Aww.
Huh,
what do you know?

09:49.356 --> 09:52.525
There's more nutritional value
in the toy than the food.

09:52.559 --> 09:55.095
♪♪

09:55.128 --> 09:58.398
[ Panting ]

09:58.431 --> 10:01.869
[ Distorted ] Come on, Dad,
you're almost there!

10:01.902 --> 10:04.738
You just got to make it
to the counter!

10:04.772 --> 10:06.740
[ Groans ]

10:06.774 --> 10:08.676
Come on,
you can make it!

10:08.709 --> 10:11.478
[ Retching ]
Mr. Dad!
What's wrong?!

10:11.511 --> 10:12.780
My heart!

10:12.813 --> 10:14.514
[ Panting ]

10:14.547 --> 10:16.116
[ Groaning ]

10:16.149 --> 10:18.085
Nah, it's cool.
It's still beating.

10:18.118 --> 10:20.654
[ Grunts ]

10:24.057 --> 10:25.392
[ Grunts ]

10:30.597 --> 10:33.300
Sir,
you've earned this.

10:33.333 --> 10:37.304
I give you...
The M'Guffin.

10:37.337 --> 10:38.405
[ Gasps ]

10:38.438 --> 10:39.940
[ Air hisses ]

10:39.973 --> 10:42.676
[ Triumphant music plays ]

10:42.710 --> 10:45.779
Look at it!

10:45.813 --> 10:48.749
It's like it's made of light!

10:48.782 --> 10:51.685
No, that's a regular burger,
just grosser than usual.

10:51.719 --> 10:53.353
Ah.

10:53.386 --> 10:56.857
[ Groaning ]
